description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Today, senior editor Joe Sobczyk looks at the president’s response to the deadly midair collision near Washington. Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Trump Quickly Jumps in on What Happened in Midair Collision

description: The dollar surged, sending currencies from Canada and Mexico plunging after President Donald Trump reiterated plans to impose 25% tariffs on imports from both US neighbors.
title: Trump’s 25% Tariff Vows Send Canada, Mexico Currencies Tumbling

description: Japan’s leader is finally set to meet Trump, three months after the US president’s election victory. Why has he spent that time cozying up to China instead?
title: Ishiba Nudges His ‘Little Japan’ Closer to China

description: President Donald Trump said he would follow through on his threat to impose 25% tariffs on imports from Canada and Mexico on Feb. 1, citing the flow of fentanyl and large trade deficits as among the reasons for his decision.
title: Trump to Hit Canada, Mexico With 25% Tariffs on Saturday

description: President Donald Trump signed an executive action he said directed federal agencies to undo diversity, equity and inclusion practices at the Department of Transportation and the Federal Aviation Administration that he has blamed as responsible for a deadly midair collision between a passenger jet and military helicopter at an airport near Washington.
title: Trump Signs Executive Action Targeting FAA Diversity Practices

description: Members of Venezuela’s most feared gang could be deported by the US to prison in El Salvador under a deal sought by President Donald Trump.
title: Trump Seeks to Send Venezuelan Gang Members to El Salvador Jails

description: Wheelchair-bound Terie Gelberg has lived at the Harborside, a retirement community on Long Island’s North Shore, for almost two decades. It was supposed to be the last home for the 99-year-old with memory issues, but plans to sell the bankrupt facility to a private equity firm threaten to upend her care.
title: Seniors Face Eviction Under Plan to Sell Retirement Home to Private Equity

description: US Defense Department employees connected their work computers to Chinese servers to access DeepSeek’s new AI chatbot for at least two days before the Pentagon moved to shut off access, according to a defense official familiar with the matter.
title: Pentagon Workers Used DeepSeek’s Chatbot for Days Before Block

description: The parents of FTX co-founder Sam Bankman-Fried are exploring ways to secure a pardon for the onetime crypto billionaire from President Donald Trump, according to a person familiar with the matter.
title: Sam Bankman-Fried’s Parents Explore Seeking Trump Pardon for Son

description: The Trump administration is poised to oust Biden-era appointee Rohit Chopra as director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau and is considering either the Treasury Department or the White House Office of Management and Budget to oversee the agency, according to people familiar with the matter.
title: Trump Team Considers Treasury or Budget Office to Oversee CFPB

description: President Donald Trump provided little new information about the cause of Wednesday’s deadly air collision in Washington between an American Airlines Group Inc. regional jet and a military helicopter, and instead blamed diversity, equity and inclusion programs.
title: Trump Attacks FAA Diversity Programs Following Mid-Air Collision

description: Friedrich Merz’s hard-line shift on migration is a calculated gambit by the German conservative leader to neutralize the far right and deliver a breakthrough with wavering voters, according to people familiar with his thinking.
title: German Conservative Hard-Line Migration Shift Is Calculated Ploy

description: Fighting between Rwandan-backed rebels and the Congolese army has placed millions of people at high risk of death from the spread of disease, Africa’s chief health advisory body said.
title: War in Congo’s East Puts Millions at Risk of Infectious Disease

description: Mozambique’s disputed October elections were “marked by anomalies and serious flaws,” the European Union’s observation mission said in a report, adding credence to widespread condemnation of the outcome from opposition parties.
title: Mozambique Election Tainted by ‘Serious Flaws,’ Observers Say

description: The European Union has re-suspended its case against China at the World Trade Organization over allegations of economic coercion targeting Lithuania, according to a filing on the WTO website.
title: EU Re-Suspends WTO Case Against China Over Economic Coercion

description: Mass protests across Serbia have exposed the cracks in the more than decade-long rule of President Aleksandar Vucic.
title: Why Mass Protests Are Testing Serbia’s Longtime Ruler

description: President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva said Brazil is prepared to respond if Donald Trump places new tariffs on the country’s products, although he hopes to improve trade relations with the US instead.
title: Brazil’s Lula Floats Retaliatory Tariffs If Trump Strikes First

description: The eastern Democratic Republic of Congo has been gripped for years by conflict that’s caused the deaths of millions of people and left multitudes displaced. The start of 2025 marked an escalation, as rebels aligned with Rwanda seized the key Congolese trading hub of Goma, threatening to trigger an all-out confrontation between the two central African nations.
title: How Rebel Advances in Congo Threaten War With Rwanda

description: Sweden presented a military aid package to Ukraine worth 13.5 billion Swedish kronor ($1.2 billion), the Nordic nation’s largest pledge to the war-torn country yet.
title: Sweden Pledges $1.2 Billion to Ukraine in Largest Package Yet

description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. faced a second day of tough questions about his nomination to head the Department of Health and Human Services, with pointed interrogation from a key senator about his shifting vaccine stance.
title: RFK Jr. Hearing Leaves Key GOP Senator ‘Struggling’ on Vote

description: OpenAI Chief Executive Officer Sam Altman briefed US policymakers on the need to continue investing heavily in physical infrastructure to support future artificial intelligence development, days after the frenzy around Chinese upstart DeepSeek cast new doubt on AI spending.
title: OpenAI’s Altman Urges US to Support AI Investment After DeepSeek

description: Blocking UNRWA leaves Gaza’s aid workers scrambling to keep services running
title: Israel Bans UN Agency After Years of Tensions Over Gaza

description: Hungarians risk jeopardizing a special relationship with the US if they vote out Prime Minister Viktor Orban in elections next year, said US President Donald Trump’s former envoy to Budapest.
title: Hungarians Risk Trump Ties If They Oust Orban, Ex-Envoy Says

description: Trump's second exit from the Paris Agreement is coming at a far shakier time for climate action, with rising populism and corporate retreat adding bigger risk to the US pullback.
title: The Global Climate Order Teeters Under Second Assault by Trump

description: El Salvador’s dollar bonds rose the most in emerging markets Thursday after lawmakers approved changes to the nation’s Bitcoin law that were needed to secure an International Monetary Fund loan.
title: El Salvador Passes Change to Bitcoin Law, Sparking Bond Rally

description: Romania’s far-right presidential frontrunner called Ukraine an “invented state” that will be dismembered after losing the war with Russia – and proceeded to make territorial claims of his own.
title: Romania’s Far-Right Candidate Dismisses Ukraine as ‘Invented’

description: Kash Patel, left, and Tulsi Gabbard.
title: Updates From Patel, Gabbard Confirmation Hearings

description: The state’s Republican farmers are an emerging force but still fear tariffs and deportations.
title: Trump’s California Water Order Does More for Farms Than Fires

description: Israel delayed the release of 110 Palestinian prisoners set for Thursday in protest over chaotic scenes during an earlier handover of hostages in Gaza to the Red Cross.
title: Israel Delays Prisoner Release After Chaotic Hostage Exchange

description: The European Union must double its defense spending as it faces at least €100 billion ($104 billion) of immediate investment needs, according to four member states that border Russia.
title: EU’s Frontline Nations See €100 Billion in Urgent Defense Needs

description: A coalition of leading African civil society groups called on the World Bank to exit its investments in for-profit hospitals, following a Bloomberg News investigation that found some facilities backed by the fund detained patients for unpaid bills and denied others emergency care until they demonstrated an ability to pay.
title: African NGOs Call on World Bank to Exit Hospital Investments

description: Czech Finance Minister Zbynek Stanjura warned against the central bank governor’s proposal to consider investing part of the country’s foreign-currency reserves in bitcoin.
title: Czech Finance Minister Warns Against Adding Bitcoin to Reserves

description: Kuwait may soon be able to sell debt for the first time in eight years, with the Council of Ministers expected to approve a new law that could enable 20 billion dinars ($65 billion) to be raised over 50 years.
title: Kuwait May Be Able to Sell First Debt Since 2017 After New Law

description: Norway’s government coalition broke apart as the two ruling partners seek to avoid losing the next parliamentary election due in seven months.
title: Norway’s Ruling Bloc Splits Ahead of Election in September

description: President Donald Trump’s tariff plans are the great unknown in the global economy right now — and it’s partly because his team is still trying to figure out what to do.
title: Trump Keeps World Waiting on Tariffs, Tries to Hash Out a Plan

description: Welcome to Balance of Power, bringing you the latest in global politics. If you haven’t yet, sign up here.
title: Brazil’s Outcast Ex-Leader Bets Big on Trump

description: Tulsi Gabbard said she refuses to be anyone’s “puppet” and promised to end what she called the weaponization of intelligence, according to prepared remarks she’s set to deliver at her confirmation hearing Thursday to be the next director of national intelligence.
title: Gabbard Says She’s No One’s ‘Puppet’ in Bid for Top Spy Job

description: Finland expects to see more damage to undersea cables in the Baltic Sea after several incidents since late 2023, President Alexander Stubb said.
title: Finland’s Stubb Says More Subsea Cable Damage Is ‘Very Likely’

description: Former Chancellor Angela Merkel weighed into Germany’s contentious election campaign, criticizing fellow Christian Democrat Friedrich Merz over his decision to force through a hard-line immigration resolution in parliament with votes from the far right.
title: Merkel Delivers Shock German Election Blow to Frontrunner Merz

description: Sweden wants to bring forward a new law that will allow authorities to secretly wiretap children under the age of 15 as the Nordic country grapples with a spate of bombings linked to criminal gangs.
title: Sweden Seeks to Fast Track New Law to Tackle Gangland Bombings

description: South African prosecutors charged former South African President Jacob Zuma’s daughter with incitement to commit terrorism over her alleged role in anti-government riots that left 354 people dead.
title: Ex-South African Leader Zuma’s Daughter Charged for Deadly Riots

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Rachel Reeves said she wants construction work to begin on a third runway at Heathrow Airport before the next election is due in 2029, a day after giving the green light to a controversial project that’s divided her governing Labour Party.
title: Reeves Wants ‘Spades in Ground’ on Heathrow Project Before 2029

description: Germany’s conservative chancellor candidate Friedrich Merz, whose CDU/CSU coalition is leading polls by double digits, upended the election campaign Wednesday by accepting votes from the nationalist Alternative for Germany to pass a hard-line migration resolution through parliament.
title: German Election Front-Runner Jolts Race With Pivot Toward AfD

description: Uganda sought to dispel fears among HIV patients that a US aid freeze will interrupt treatment and promised that such programs will continue.
title: Uganda Reassures HIV Patients of Care Despite Trump’s Aid Order

description: Rwandan President Paul Kagame accused his South African counterpart of “lies” and “distortion” over comments about the conflict in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, ratcheting up tensions between the two leaders amid regional efforts to secure a ceasefire.
title: Ramaphosa, Kagame Trade Barbs Over Rwanda-Backed Siege in Congo

description: Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. said he wants to meet with US President Donald Trump to discuss immigration policy amid reports that some Filipinos are at risk of deportation.
title: Philippines’ Marcos Seeks Trump Meeting to Discuss Immigration

description: France’s economy contracted at the end of last year as tailwinds from the Paris Olympics faded and a government collapse bruised confidence among businesses and consumers.
title: French Economy Shrinks as Political Mayhem Erodes Confidence

description: The EU sees a trade clash as inevitable and has prepared a list of US goods to hit with duties in retaliation.
title: Trump Threats Risk Stretching Europe's Fragile Unity to Breaking Point

description: The UK wants trustbusters to weigh economic growth alongside preserving competition. But merger control works best with a narrow consumer focus.
title: Protecting Consumers Is Not Anti-Growth

description: French lawmakers on Thursday will try to reach a budget compromise that can get enough support to avert another government collapse and restore financial certainty for the country.
title: France’s Budget Bill Nears Cliff Edge in Parliamentary Talks

description: The summer of 1989, when soldiers shot and killed hundreds and possibly thousands of demonstrators in Beijing’s historic Tiananmen Square, helped shape China into the security state it is today.
title: DeepSeek Doesn’t Want to Talk About Tiananmen Square. Here’s What to Know

description: Palestinian Authority Prime Minister Mohammad Mustafa said his government plans to rebuild Gaza with help from the US and Saudi Arabia, a process he said would reshape the Middle East and require the removal of Hamas from power and Israel from the ground.
title: Palestinian Premier Says He’ll Rebuild Gaza With Trump’s Help

description: Democratic Republic of Congo President Felix Tshisekedi, speaking publicly for the first time since Rwandan-backed rebels seized the eastern city of Goma, said his government was preparing a response and warned of “unpredictable consequences” for the region.
title: Congo President Vows ‘Resistance’ Over Rebel Seizure of Key City

description: The White House received more than 7,400 requests for credentials one day after saying it would open press briefings to content creators, influencers and podcasters.
title: Over 7,400 Influencers Apply for White House Press Credentials

description: It’s not a skip, it’s a pause — and maybe an extended one.
title: Powell Signals Fed on Hold as Trump’s Economic Policies Take Shape

description: President Donald Trump has boasted about bringing a more transactional approach to his relationship with world leaders. Just over a week into his second term, many have shown they’re eager to make the deals he treasures.
title: Trump’s Transactional Foreign Policy Leads to Flurry of Pledges
